This is a known breaking change. In .NET 10, MAUI adopted **edge-to-edge** rendering on Android, which makes the old `adjustResize` soft input mode ineffective. The layout no longer automatically shrinks when the keyboard appears.

**Recommended fix — handle IME (keyboard) insets in your Android platform code:**

**`Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:**
```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Android.OS.Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Ensure edge-to-edge insets are dispatched
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
            Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!,
            new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }
}

class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var systemBar = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());

        // Push content up by the keyboard height
        v.SetPadding(
            systemBar.Left,
            systemBar.Top,
            systemBar.Right,
            Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, systemBar.Bottom));

        return insets;
    }
}
```

**Your XAML layout (chat screen):**
```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" ... />

    <!-- Input bar stays above keyboard -->
    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" Command="{Binding SendCommand}" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

**Key points:**
- The `WindowInsets` listener dynamically adjusts the bottom padding of your root content view to match the keyboard height.
- No need for `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust` at all — it's the deprecated Android path.
- `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (enabled by default in MAUI) helps with scrolling focused fields into view, but for a fixed-bottom input bar, inset handling is what you want.

If you also need iOS support, iOS still uses `adjustResize`-equivalent behavior by default via MAUI, so no extra work is needed there.
